- **`"2,5m"` and `"5.5m"`** grouped under non-integer values — covers locale-style decimals and floats.
- **`"90s"`/`"120m"`** assert that no clock-style normalization happens (the spec only says "total seconds," never that components wrap at 60).
- The `import` line assumes a module named `duration`; adjust to wherever `parse_duration` is defined in your codebase.

